      "manualSections": [
        {
          "heading": "🧩 x-toggle — toggle a class on a target element",
          "html": "  <p>Distinct from the <code>&lt;wb-toggle&gt;</code> switch component under Form Controls — this toggles an arbitrary CSS class on any target.</p>\n  <wb-demo>\n    <button x-toggle target=\"#toggle-box\">Toggle Class</button>\n    <div id=\"toggle-box\" style=\"width: 50px; height: 50px; background: red; margin-top: 1rem; transition: all 0.3s;\"></div>\n  </wb-demo>"
        },
        {
          "heading": "🎨 Theme & Dark Mode",
          "id": "theme-dark-mode",
          "html": "<p id=\"semanticstheme-p-13\">Behaviors for managing themes and dark mode.</p>\n\n  <!-- THEME CONTROL -->\n  <h2 id=\"semanticstheme-h2-14\">Theme Control <code id=\"semanticstheme-code-15\">wb-themecontrol</code></h2>\n  <div id=\"semanticstheme-div-16\" class=\"demo-section\">\n    <p id=\"semanticstheme-p-17\">A dropdown to switch the global theme. Persists selection to localStorage.</p>\n    <wb-demo>\n      <wb-themecontrol></wb-themecontrol>\n    </wb-demo>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- DARK MODE ENFORCER -->\n  <h2 id=\"semanticstheme-h2-19\">Forced Theme <code id=\"semanticstheme-code-20\">x-darkmode</code></h2>\n  <div id=\"semanticstheme-div-21\" class=\"demo-section\">\n    <p id=\"semanticstheme-p-22\">These sections have forced themes regardless of the global setting. <code>target=\"self\"</code> scopes the theme to the element itself; <code>theme=\"…\"</code> sets which theme (not <code>data-theme</code>, which <code>x-darkmode</code> doesn't read).</p>\n\n    <wb-demo>\n      <div\n        class=\"card\"\n        x-darkmode\n        target=\"self\"\n        theme=\"dark\">\n        <h3>Forced Dark Mode</h3>\n        <p>This card will always be dark.</p>\n        <button variant=\"primary\">Primary Button</button>\n      </div>\n    </wb-demo>\n\n    <wb-demo>\n      <div\n        class=\"card\"\n        x-darkmode\n        target=\"self\"\n        theme=\"light\">\n        <h3>Forced Light Mode</h3>\n        <p>This card will always be light.</p>\n        <button variant=\"primary\">Primary Button</button>\n      </div>\n    </wb-demo>\n\n    <wb-demo>\n      <div\n        class=\"card\"\n        x-darkmode\n        target=\"self\"\n        theme=\"cyberpunk\">\n        <h3>Forced Cyberpunk</h3>\n        <p>This card will always be cyberpunk.</p>\n        <button variant=\"primary\">Primary Button</button>\n      </div>\n    </wb-demo>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- NESTED THEMES -->\n  <h2 id=\"semanticstheme-h2-35\">Nested Themes</h2>\n  <div id=\"semanticstheme-div-36\" class=\"demo-section\">\n    <p>Themes cascade through <code>data-theme</code> on any container — no behavior needed, just the plain HTML attribute the theme system itself keys off of. A nested container can override its ancestor's theme.</p>\n\n    <wb-demo>\n      <div data-theme=\"forest\">\n        <h3>Forest Theme Container</h3>\n        <p>This container uses <code>data-theme=\"forest\"</code> directly in HTML.</p>\n\n        <div class=\"card\">\n          <h4>Inherited Forest Card</h4>\n          <button variant=\"primary\">Forest Button</button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"card\" data-theme=\"sunset\">\n          <h4>Nested Sunset Card</h4>\n          <p>Overriding parent theme with <code>data-theme=\"sunset\"</code>.</p>\n          <button variant=\"primary\">Sunset Button</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </wb-demo>\n  </div>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
